scheduled_maintenances.name: Anypoint Platform Release and Maintenance Window

incident_updates.body:
US: On Saturday, Oct 28, 2023 between 9AM and 2PM PDT (12PM - 5PM EDT, 4PM - 9PM UTC)
Bug fixes & back-end performance enhancement releases
Anypoint Runtime Manager will be performing a webserver configuration change for the UI.
Customer Impacting / Downtime Announcement(s)
ATTENTION: up to 1 hour of service interruption is expected.
We will be performing a scheduled upgrade of an internal database. *** Service Impact Details: ** Applications: - Anypoint API Designer - Mocking service - Anypoint Flow Designer - Anypoint Exchange - Anypoint Studio - MuleSoft Composer and Composer for Salesforce * User Experience(UX): User Interface (UI) will display errors when: - API Designer: projects are listed, opened or created. - Mocking service: upon interaction within API Designer. - Flow Designer: users want to list their connections or configurations. - Exchange: assets are published, deleted, and when asset portals are read or modified. Also, when asset publication is triggered - Studio: creating an API project, importing an API Specification from Design Center, pulling or pushing from API projects synchronized with Design Center, or downloading a RAML from Design Center to a Mule Project. - Composer: flows are listed, opened or created. * API Calls: REST API calls for asset publication won't work. * Existing Runtimes: are not impacted.
*** ATTENTION: up to 2 hours of service interruption is expected during this maintenance window for the following ***
We will be doing a scheduled upgrade on Access Management database. *** Service Impact Details: * Applications: - Access Management - Help Center During maintenance window - Anypoint users will not be able to login to their account. Any user that has already logged in 1 hour prior to the downtime window will be able to login and will only be able to view information, but not be able to make any modifications in Access Management until the scheduled downtime is complete. - Will not be able to obtain new access tokens. Any tokens obtained 1 hour prior to the downtime window will not expire until the end of the downtime window. If you have access tokens, you may be able to access read APIs but not write APIs. - Users will not be able to login so will not be able to create tickets in Help Center. - API calls to Access Management may be errored out. Following maintenance downtime - Access Management will function as usual - Help Center will function as usual Additionally, the following services will be impacted and in degraded states during this change. It is recommended that customers treat the following services as degraded during this window: - API Designer - API Analytics - API Monitoring Center - Anypoint Flash - API Functional Monitoring - Audit Log - Composer (MuleSoft and Salesforce) - Design Center Projects - API Mocking Service - Connectivity Framework - OAuth Client System - Anypoint MQ - Anypoint Metering - Runtime Fabric - Runtime Manager - RPA - Anypoint Partner Manager v2 - Object Store V2 - Service Mesh - Tokenization - Trusted Domains - Universal Management Platform - Existing running applications won't see any impact. If an existing (MQ or OSv2 app) got restarted during the maintenance, it won't be impacted either. - Customers won't be able to deploy new MQ and OSv2 apps when Auth Service database is in RO mode as authentication tokens can't be generated.
*** ATTENTION: up to 3 hours of service interruption is expected during this maintenance window for the following ***
We will be doing a scheduled upgrade on Anypoint Monitoring and Visualizer databases. *** Service Impact Details: * Applications: - Anypoint Monitoring - Anypoint Visualizer During maintenance downtime - Anypoint Monitoring users will not be able to create, update or delete alerts and custom dashboards. - Anypoint Visualizer users will not be able to see topography
*** ATTENTION: up to 2 minutes of service interruption is expected during this maintenance window for the following ***
We will be doing a scheduled upgrade on a Cloudhub 2.0 databases. *** Service Impact Details: * Applications: - Cloudhub 2.0 During maintenance downtime - Customers may not be able to view VPN configurations for a private space - Private Space Creation may fail during the 2 minute window - Private Space provisioning or updating may be delayed while the database is failing over
***ATTENTION: up to 60 minutes of service interruption is expected.***
We will be performing a scheduled upgrade of an internal database. *** Service Impact Details: * Applications: - API Manager During maintenance downtime: - Runtimes: are not affected. - User Interface (UI): will show “Unable to complete this request while services are undergoing maintenance. Please retry after maintenance has been completed.” when doing certain operations. - API calls: to these services will return Service Unavailable Error (503). GET Request will not be affected. - Logs and Data: will continue to be collected. Following maintenance downtime: - Logs and Data: will appear as usual. - Runtimes and all services: will resume normal operation.
